1�Oh my Gob! You're one of those adventurerurers, aren't ya?You got nothin' on me, ?[man./lady.] I was just mindin' my own businesesess, lookin' for junk an' stuff.
1�Hey, watch out. You don't wanna fight me. I'll turn you into meat jerky!Wait, how about you and me be friends instead? Sound good?
1�I travel all over the world and hear lots of differererent stories. I even hear your stories. I can tell you one, if you want.

1�Now, listen close...
1�I am Lerene, a researcher of sorts who travels Vana'diel, studying ancient ruins.What brings you to this dreadful place?
1�My my, if only you knew how it does my heart good to see another living soul!
1�How odd. I can't shake this feeling that we've met somewhere before.
1�My name is Er...Err...Lerene. I'm a bit of a researcher.
1�My name is, err...Lerene. I visit ruins all around Vana'diel in pursuit of ancient knowledge.
1�Ra'Kaznar is positively overflowing with all manner of shadows. If we don't keep their numbers under control, they might spill out into the wildlands.
1�If they were just feral fiends, I'd say throw caution to the wind and cull them right now, but I sense that there's some greater presence guiding them.

1�I'd advise you to take care of the mystical barricades that line this place should you decide to take the beasts on. Those ??doors?? have a mind of their own, and are apt to trap you within the labyrinth.
1�It's as if the walls themselves are alive, with energies pulsing through their cracks like the blood in our veins.
1�And those energies are no ordinary magic. You could try to rend them to tatters with a greataxe, but the only thing to splinter would be its hilt.
1�If your goal is to colonize this land, then you'll need to find a way to deal with such obstacles. I'll do a little bit of experimentation and see if I can find anything.
1�And by ??I,?? I mean ??we.?? I would expect no less.
1�If you find something with traces of arcane energies, come back to me. Perhaps I can learn more about its form and function.
1�With any luck, I'll be able to fashion a paten that'll turn the energies to our benefit.
1�??What's a paten??? A paten is a magical apparatus that converts cyclical magic into simple formulas.
1�Leave the details to me--for you, a grasp of the basics will suffice.
1�First things first. Find something with remnants of this energy and bring it back here. Then we can get it to work.
1�I would venture two %???? should suffice.
1�If I'm right, the shadows wandering about the inner court should have some on them.
1�Will you assist Lerene?Yes. I've got to.Defeat monsters? Not my thing.
1�Excellent! The two of us will make the perfect team.
1�Not your thing? But then how...?<Sigh> I suppose I can't ask you to risk life and limb.
1�The shadows located here within Ra'Kaznar have got to have what I seek. I can feel it.
1�The more you bring back, the easier it'll be for me to make the paten. Let's see...a total of two %???? should suffice.
1�Welcome back. I trust you have found enough %?????
1�Aha...6...So this is how it functions.
1�Remember how I explained that magic coursed through the cracks like blood through our veins?
1�Then if we found a way to reverse the flow...
1�Of course, this is all just theory. We won't know until we actually try it, hmm?
1�My professor always told me ??To know is to act!?? Knowledge is nothing until you put it into practice.
1�Let me prepare the paten using the sigils you have brought me. Just give me a moment...
1�Splendid! This should assist you in getting rid of that pesky magic impeding your progress.
1�Come with me to the lower levels, and we will test it out together.
1�I'll bring along 6????, which will enable us to operate the transit device. Shall we?
1�If it doesn't work, then we won't be able to figure out how the door operates...which leads us into a terrible loop of unknowns.
1�Steel yourself for action!
1�Hmm...I suppose that accomplished something, but we're not done yet.Let me just fiddle with...
1�Open up, you piece of--
1�Owowowowow!
1�W-well, at least we reversed the magic. All you have to do is give it a couple of good bashes, and that should break it right off its hinges.
1�But you're a pioneer, right? So what's a little blood?
1�I, on the other hand, am much more delicate. Let me put my handiwork to the test and make you a paten of your own.
1�Even the burning sun of ignorance cannot evaporate the fountain of knowledge. The rest I leave in your capable hands.
1�After all, there is more research to be done!
1�Now, just how is it that the paten doesn't work...?
1�Oh! You must be a geomancer. Am I right?
1�Then you wouldn't go anywhere without your trusty luopan?
1�Wonderful! Did you know that the techniques used in making it have been passed down through the ages?
1�But I suppose you aren't interested in a scholarly lesson. I could use a bit of your geomantic energies, if you could spare the time.
1�If you are capable of feeling the lifestream, then you must be able to channel the powers latent in this tree.
1�Good to hear. Let me explain my hypothesis:
1�Quite a shame, indeed. I'm certain we could learn much from this discovery.
1�The roots of this tree are protected--or perhaps a better phrase would be ??sealed in??--by the magic enshrouding Ra'Kaznar.
1�What I require is that you lay your luopan by its side and invoke a Geocolure ritual.
1�Once that is done, I will invoke a Cure spell in the hopes that the roots will absorb the healing energy, thus weakening the seal.
1�Finally, you will unleash the power of your luopan to shatter the bonds.
1�This should enable us to get to the underbelly of this mystery. How does the saying go? ??Let the cat out of the bag???
1�Sorry for the long-winded explanation. Are you ready?
1�Okay!
..�It worked!

s!�This is superb! I must make detailed records of what has transpired here.Thank you, pioneer!
